      "*": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b><a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">Home</a> * <a href=\"/People\" title=\"People\">People</a> * Zach Wegner</b>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:302px;\"><a href=\"http://www.csvn.nl/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=472%3Afoto-impressie-wcccwcsc-kanazawa-japan&amp;catid=51%3Atoernooien&amp;Itemid=28&amp;lang=en\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/images/thumb/4/4b/ZachWegnerWCCC2010.jpg/300px-ZachWegnerWCCC2010.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"229\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"/images/4/4b/ZachWegnerWCCC2010.jpg 1.5x\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/File:ZachWegnerWCCC2010.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Zach Wegner, <a href=\"/WCCC_2010\" title=\"WCCC 2010\">WCCC 2010</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup></div></div></div> \n<p><b>Zach Wegner</b>,<br />\nan American software engineer and computer chess programmer based in <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Austin,_Texas\">Austin, TX</a>. He has been involved in CC since starting his first program in 2002, at the age of 14 <sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>.  He is the author of <a href=\"/ZCT\" title=\"ZCT\">ZCT</a>, an <a href=\"/Category:Open_Source\" title=\"Category:Open Source\">open source engine</a> written in <a href=\"/C\" title=\"C\">C</a>, and author of <a href=\"/Rondo\" title=\"Rondo\">Rondo</a>, the continuation of <a href=\"/Anthony_Cozzie\" title=\"Anthony Cozzie\">Anthony Cozzie's</a> <a href=\"/Zappa\" title=\"Zappa\">Zappa</a>. Zach has been an organizer here at <a href=\"/Main_Page\" title=\"Main Page\">CPW</a> when he was active in computerchess until 2011!\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><div class=\"toctitle\"><h2>Contents</h2></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Rybka_Case\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Rybka Case</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Rondo\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Rondo</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Forum_Posts\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Forum Posts</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#2002_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2002 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#2004_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2004 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-6\"><a href=\"#2006_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2006 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-7\"><a href=\"#2008_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2008 ...</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-8\"><a href=\"#2010_...\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3.5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">2010 ...</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-9\"><a href=\"#External_Links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">4</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External Links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-10\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">5</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rybka_Case\">Rybka Case</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zach_Wegner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Rybka Case\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>Zach Wegner was skeptic by <a href=\"/Vasik_Rajlich\" title=\"Vasik Rajlich\">Vasik Rajlich's</a> statements on the origins of <a href=\"/Rybka\" title=\"Rybka\">Rybka 1.0 beta</a> and its influence from <a href=\"/Fruit\" title=\"Fruit\">Fruit</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-3\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-3\">&#91;3&#93;</a></sup>, to investigate and compare disassembled Rybka with Fruit. He published some results on <a href=\"/Evaluation\" title=\"Evaluation\">evaluation</a> in 2010 <sup id=\"cite_ref-4\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-4\">&#91;4&#93;</a></sup>.\n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Rondo\">Rondo</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zach_Wegner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Rondo\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<p>In 2010, Zach collaborated with <a href=\"/Anthony_Cozzie\" title=\"Anthony Cozzie\">Anthony Cozzie</a>, who, still in computer chess retirement, has given control for further development of his massive parallel program <a href=\"/Zappa\" title=\"Zappa\">Zappa</a> to Zach. The new project <a href=\"/Rondo\" title=\"Rondo\">Rondo</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-5\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-5\">&#91;5&#93;</a></sup> was registered for the <a href=\"/WCCC_2010\" title=\"WCCC 2010\">WCCC 2010</a> <sup id=\"cite_ref-6\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-6\">&#91;6&#93;</a></sup>. Rondo became strong runner up in both the open hardware WCCC 2010 behind <a href=\"/Rybka\" title=\"Rybka\">Rybka</a>, and the uniform hardware <a href=\"/WCSC_2010\" title=\"WCSC 2010\">WCSC 2010</a> close behind <a href=\"/Shredder\" title=\"Shredder\">Shredder</a>. Rondo was declared <a href=\"/Rybka_Controversy#2010\" title=\"Rybka Controversy\">joint champion</a> along with <a href=\"/Thinker\" title=\"Thinker\">Thinker</a> after the <a href=\"/World_Computer_Chess_Championship#RybkaDisqualification\" title=\"World Computer Chess Championship\">disqualification</a> of <a href=\"/Rybka\" title=\"Rybka\">Rybka</a> by the <a href=\"/ICGA\" title=\"ICGA\">ICGA</a> in June 2011. \n</p>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Forum_Posts\">Forum Posts</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zach_Wegner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Forum Posts\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2002_...\">2002 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zach_Wegner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: 2002 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=246067\">BitBoard q</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 18, 2002 <sup id=\"cite_ref-7\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-7\">&#91;7&#93;</a></sup>&#160;» <a href=\"/Bitboards\" title=\"Bitboards\">Bitboards</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2004_...\">2004 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zach_Wegner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: 2004 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;t=171&amp;start=143\">Re: Attack table</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, October 22, 2004&#160;» <a href=\"/Attack_and_Defend_Maps\" title=\"Attack and Defend Maps\">Attack and Defend Maps</a>, <a href=\"/Node_Types\" title=\"Node Types\">Node Types</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.stmintz.com/ccc/index.php?id=417486\">Re: Smallest chess program in chess is in basic</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, March 19, 2005</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2006_...\">2006 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zach_Wegner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=6\" title=\"Edit section: 2006 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=26851&amp;t=4523\">Zach's tricky 32-bit approach</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, August 22, 2006&#160;» <a href=\"/Kindergarten_Bitboards\" title=\"Kindergarten Bitboards\">Kindergarten Bitboards</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.open-aurec.com/wbforum/viewtopic.php?f=4&amp;t=5623&amp;p=27838\">Yet another new bitboard move generation method</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/Computer_Chess_Forums\" title=\"Computer Chess Forums\">Winboard Forum</a>, September 22, 2006&#160;» <a href=\"/Titboards\" title=\"Titboards\">Titboards</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2008_...\">2008 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zach_Wegner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=7\" title=\"Edit section: 2008 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=19446\">If making an SMP engine, do NOT use processes</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, February 07, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Parallel_Search\" title=\"Parallel Search\">Parallel Search</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=21343\">Semi-Path Dependent Hashing: a semi-useless idea</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 24, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Repetitions\" title=\"Repetitions\">Repetitions</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=22542\">Old CCC archives?</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, July 24, 2008</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=23118\">Rybka 1.0 vs. Strelka</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 19, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Rybka\" title=\"Rybka\">Rybka</a>, <a href=\"/Strelka\" title=\"Strelka\">Strelka</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=23249\">Questions for Vas</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 25, 2008&#160;» <a href=\"/Vasik_Rajlich\" title=\"Vasik Rajlich\">Vasik Rajlich</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=245932&amp;t=26152\">Re: Zobrist key random numbers</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, January 22, 2009&#160;» <a href=\"/Zobrist_Hashing\" title=\"Zobrist Hashing\">Zobrist Hashing</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=28212\">ZCT 0.3.2500 released</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 02, 2009 </li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29269\">Bit twiddlement question: greater of two popcounts</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 06, 2009&#160;» <a href=\"/Bit-Twiddling\" title=\"Bit-Twiddling\">Bit-Twiddling</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=29333\">Bit twiddling question, part 2: arbitrary bitscan order</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, August 11, 2009</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"2010_...\">2010 ...</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zach_Wegner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=8\" title=\"Edit section: 2010 ...\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?topic_view=threads&amp;p=351606&amp;t=34561\">Re: DTS Structure</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, May 29, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/Iterative_Search\" title=\"Iterative Search\">Iterative Search</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=34749\">Zach, is this true?</a> by <a href=\"/Gabor_Szots\" title=\"Gabor Szots\">Gabor Szots</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 06, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=34782&amp;start=7\">Re: An extremely interesting topic...</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, June 07, 2010</li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=36174\">WCCC games</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 25, 2010&#160;» <a href=\"/WCCC_2010\" title=\"WCCC 2010\">WCCC 2010</a> </li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.talkchess.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=40333\">Haswell New Instructions</a> by <a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">Zach Wegner</a>, <a href=\"/CCC\" title=\"CCC\">CCC</a>, September 09, 2011&#160;» <a href=\"/BMI2#PDEPBitboards\" title=\"BMI2\">BMI2 PEXT/PDEP Bitboards</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_Links\">External Links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zach_Wegner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=9\" title=\"Edit section: External Links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<ul><li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://www.game-ai-forum.org/icga-tournaments/person.php?id=656\">Zach Wegner's ICGA Tournaments</a></li>\n<li> <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"https://github.com/zwegner\">zwegner (Zach Wegner) · GitHub</a></li></ul>\n<h1><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/index.php?title=Zach_Wegner&amp;action=edit&amp;section=10\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h1>\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">↑</a></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://www.csvn.nl/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=472%3Afoto-impressie-wcccwcsc-kanazawa-japan&amp;catid=51%3Atoernooien&amp;Itemid=28&amp;lang=en\">Foto-impressie WCCC/WCSC Kanazawa, Japan</a> by <a href=\"/Jan_Krabbenbos\" title=\"Jan Krabbenbos\">Jan Krabbenbos</a> from the <a href=\"/CSVN\" title=\"CSVN\">CSVN site</a></span>\n</li>\n<li id=\"cite_note-2\"><span 